    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are given a list of events, each event has the following fields:\n\n* Date (in MM/DD/YYYY format)\n* Event Name\n* Day (e.g., Monday, Tuesday, etc.)\n* Public Holiday (either \"Yes\" or \"No\")\n* Comments (optional)\n* Status (either \"Yes\" or \"No\")\n* Add newline in messages as \\\\n\n\nThe current date is  {{ $json['Readable date'] }}.\nThe date format is MM/DD/YYYY.\n---\n\nYour Tasks:\n\n1. Parse each event's Date field as an actual date.\n2. Filter the events to include only those where: \n- The Date falls between {{ $json['Readable date'] }} and 14 days after that date, inclusive \nAND\n- The Status field is \"No\"\n3. Strictly follow rule 2.\n4. From the filtered list, select the single earliest event by date.\n5. Based on the \"Public Holiday\" field:\n   - If **\"Yes\"**, assign it to **Group A (Public Holiday)**\n   - If **\"No\"**, assign it to **Group B (Internal Event)**\n6. For the selected event, generate an object with:\n   - Date  \n   - Event Name  \n   - Day  \n   - Public Holiday  \n   - Comments  \n   - formattedDate (e.g., \"Friday, September 5th 2025\")  \n   - teamMessage  \n   - clientMessage  \n\n---\n\nEmoji Rules:\n\nUse relevant emojis for better engagement and clarity:\n- Public Holiday: 📢, 📅, 🏛️, 💤  \n- Internal Events: 🎉, 📅, 🏏 (Cricket), 🍽️ (Lunch), 🧠 (Training), etc.\n\nEmoji Placement:\n- Add at the **start** of subject/reminder lines\n- Optionally surround event names\n- Keep it professional and minimal\n\n---\n\nMessage Templates:\n\n### 🏛️ Team Message – Public Holiday (Group A)\n\nIf the event is on **Monday–Friday**:\n📢 *Reminder: Upcoming Public Event – Event Name* \n\nPlease be informed that, in observance of *Event Name* on formattedDate, our office will remain closed for the entire day. Kindly plan accordingly. Please notify clients about the day off in advance to ensure smooth communication.\n\nIf the event is on **Saturday or Sunday**:\n📢 *Reminder: Upcoming Public Event – Event Name*\n\nPlease be informed that, in observance of *Event Name* on formattedDate, our office will remain closed for the entire day.\n\n---\n\n### 🎉 Team Message – Internal Event (Group B)\n\n🎉 *Reminder: Upcoming Internal Event – Event Name*  \n\nPlease note that the *Event Name* is scheduled for *formattedDate*. Kindly manage your work schedule accordingly to participate and make the most of this fun event.\n\n---\n\n### 📨 Client Message – All Events\n\nSubject: Service Update – Event Name  \n\nDear [Client Name],  \nWe wanted to give you advance notice that our team will be participating in *Event Name* on *formattedDate*.  \nWhile we'll maintain essential services, there may be slight delays in response times during this period. We appreciate your understanding and will ensure any urgent matters are handled promptly.  \n\nThank you for your continued partnership.  \nBest regards,\n---\n\nOutput Format:\n\nIf the event is a **Public Holiday**:\n```json\n{\n  \"publicHolidayEvents\": [ { ...event object with teamMessage and clientMessage } ],\n  \"internalEvents\": []\n}\nIf the event is an Internal Event:\n{\n  \"publicHolidayEvents\": [],\n  \"internalEvents\": [ { ...event object with teamMessage and clientMessage } ]\n}\nIf no valid events, return:\n{\n  \"publicHolidayEvents\": [],\n  \"internalEvents\": []\n}\n\nRespond only with the final JSON object and nothing else.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
